### About

Overview:

> The Central Statistics office is responsible for the collection, compilation, extraction and dissemination for statistical purposes of information relating to economic, social and general activities and conditions in the State

### Access

Available on website, as well as through web interface for generating data file. Multiple formats available.

### Data

Full list of topics at:

 * <http://www.cso.ie/statistics/>

### Openness

Not open. Noncommercial use requires permission - as does using a 'significant volume' of material. [Legal](http://www.cso.ie/aboutus/rightspermiss.htm) page says:

> Reproduction of short extracts of this copyrighted site for such purposes as criticism, comment, newsreporting, teaching, scholarship and research for non-commercial purposes is also free of charge and may be undertaken without further request, provided that the statistics are reproduced accurately and the CSO is credited as the source.

> Users who wish to publish, in any medium, a significant volume of material extracted from the content of this site shall seek copyright permission from information@cso.ie.

> Users are not permitted to use any part of the content of this site to develop or derive any data product or data service for distribution or commercial sale without a licence to do so. For information on existing licensing arrangements please contact information@cso.ie.
